Tax Modelling

TXModel <- subset.data.frame(CPAData, !is.na(CPAData$NextCourse) & CPAData$NextCourse == 'TX')

TXModel <-  dataLong(dataSet = TXModel, timeColumn = "SemestersBetween", censColumn = "NextRegStatus_Binary")

TXModel$timeInt_Num <-  as.numeric(TXModel$timeInt)

#Create new DateCode and Semester variables for datalong format
TXModel$DateCode_DataLong <-  (2.5*((TXModel$timeInt_Num)-1) + TXModel$DateCode)
TXModel$TimeCode_DataLong <- TXModel$DateCode_DataLong %% 10

TXModel$Semester_DataLong[TXModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 0]   <- "Spring"
TXModel$Semester_DataLong[TXModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 2.5] <- "Summer"
TXModel$Semester_DataLong[TXModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 5]   <- "Fall"
TXModel$Semester_DataLong[TXModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 7.5] <- "Winter"
TXModel$Semester_DataLong <- as.factor(TXModel$Semester_DataLong)

TXMaximalModelFit <-  glm(formula = y ~ timeInt
                        + ExamLocation
                        + BusinessProvince
                        + PrereqGPA
                        + Employer_Cat
                        + LegacyPath
                        + Level
                        + FieldofStudy
                        + Major
                        + ExperienceRoute
                        + Role
                        + Gender
                        + Age
                        + Semester_DataLong
                        , data = TXModel, family = binomial())

Anova(TXMaximalModelFit, type = "II", test = "Wald")

KMfit_TX <- survfit(Surv(SemestersBetween, NextRegStatus_Binary) ~ 1, data = TXModel)

Assurance Modelling

ASModel <- subset.data.frame(CPAData, !is.na(CPAData$NextCourse) & CPAData$NextCourse == 'AS')

ASModel <-  dataLong(dataSet = ASModel, timeColumn = "SemestersBetween", censColumn = "NextRegStatus_Binary")

ASModel$timeInt_Num <-  as.numeric(ASModel$timeInt)

#Create new DateCode and Semester variables for datalong format
ASModel$DateCode_DataLong <-  (2.5*((ASModel$timeInt_Num)-1) + ASModel$DateCode)
ASModel$TimeCode_DataLong <- ASModel$DateCode_DataLong %% 10

ASModel$Semester_DataLong[ASModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 0]   <- "Spring"
ASModel$Semester_DataLong[ASModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 2.5] <- "Summer"
ASModel$Semester_DataLong[ASModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 5]   <- "Fall"
ASModel$Semester_DataLong[ASModel$TimeCode_DataLong == 7.5] <- "Winter"
ASModel$Semester_DataLong <- as.factor(ASModel$Semester_DataLong)

ASMaximalModelFit <-  glm(formula = y ~ timeInt
                        + ExamLocation
                        + BusinessProvince
                        + PrereqGPA
                        + Employer_Cat
                        + LegacyPath
                        + Level
                        + FieldofStudy
                        + Major
                        + ExperienceRoute
                        + Role
                        + Gender
                        + Age
                        + Semester_DataLong
                        , data = ASModel, family = binomial())

Anova(ASMaximalModelFit, type = "II", test = "Wald")
